{
  "doc_id": "47613",
  "text": "Transcription factor EB (TFEB), which mediates lysosomal biogenesis and promotes macroautophagy, is sequestered by ␣Syn in both human PD brain tissue and in a rat PD model [CITATION_1] . In the rat model, overexpressing ␣Syn is associated with dysfunctional macroautophagy, increased SNc DA neurodegeneration, and impaired motor function. However, these deficits can all be ameliorated by overexpressing TFEB or Beclin-1 (another autophagy regulator), suggesting that macroautophagy can be upregulated in PD to reduce ␣Syn aggregation and neurodegeneration [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
